Three tables join for order details.
Tables: customers, orders, products
Get customer_name, product_name, amount

SELECT c.customer_name, p.product_name, o.amount
FROM customers c
INNER JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
INNER JOIN products p ON o.product_id = p.product_id;

I used INNER JOIN because I only wanted records 
where there is a valid relationship between customers, orders, and products. 
First, I joined customers with orders using customer_id, 
then I joined orders with products using product_id. 
This returns only orders that have both a valid customer and a valid product.
